The paper deals with optimization problems and their LP relaxations, which are typically studied in the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of monotone circuits and their connection to extended formulations suggest that the paper may also be relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The study of cover inequalities and their integrality gaps is related to the field of combinatorial optimization, which falls under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the use of circuits and their depth suggests a possible connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning), which often involves the study of neural networks and their architectures.
